codex
I found a concrete generalization gap: we only emit trailing-punctuation slots when punctuation exists, so most U.S.C. sections omit a deterministic “false/0” signal. I’ll patch decompiler+codec to always emit `*_has_trailing_punct` and `*_trailing_punct_count`, then add focused regression asserts and rerun the slot tests.
